>> To Check The Text Base Consoles
	press ctrl+alt+f2
		to
	press ctrl+alt+f6

>> To Check The Terminal Type
	tty

>>To Check The Graphical Console
	press ctrl+alt+f1

>>To Change The Dir
	cd
  
>>To Open The Terminal With Command
	press alt+f2
	then write gnome-terminal on console
  
>>To Maximize and Minimize the Terminal
	press f11
  
>>To Increase The Font Size
	press ctrl+shift+plus
  
>>To Decrease The Font Size
	ctrl+minus
  
>>To Open The Terminal
	*right click on desktop
	*click on open terminal
  
>>To check the present working DIR
	pwd
  
>>To check the contains of pwd
	ls
  
>>To check The Contains Of Pwd
	ls
  
>>To Check The Proporties Of Files
	ls -l
  
>>To Check The Hideen Files
	ls -a
  
>>To Check The INode Number
	ls -i
  
>>To Create A File

	cat>linux
	this is linux
	press enter
	press ctrl+d(to save & quit)

>>To Read A fILE
	cat linux
  
>>To Appand A File
	cat >> linux
	this is another line
	press enter
	press ctrl+d(to save & quit)

>>Cat linux(to read the file)
	cat linux

>>To Create A Multiple Files
	touch v1 v2 v3 v4 v5
	ls to check newly created file



